The paper deals with the problem of online or recursive robust PCA, which involves recovering a low-rank matrix from its sparse and dense components. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). Given that the paper focuses on the performance guarantees of a specific algorithm for this problem, it is likely to be classified under one or more of these sub-categories. Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely, as they are directly related to the problem of low-rank matrix recovery and have the largest number of papers in this area. The other sub-categories are also relevant, as they deal with related aspects of the problem, such as numerical stability, convergence analysis, and complexity analysis.
